Calochortus albus, commonly known as the white mariposa lily, is a species of flowering plant in the lily family.
It is native to California and Oregon in the United States.
The plant grows from a bulb and can reach heights of up to 3 feet.
The flowers are white with yellow or purple markings and are shaped like tulips.
The leaves are narrow and grass-like in appearance.
It is commonly found in grassy areas, meadows, and open woods.
The white mariposa lily is often used as an ornamental plant in gardens and landscaping.
